<%# locals: (user:, summary: nil) -%>
<%# Visually-hidden span referenced by the avatar button's
    `aria-labelledby`. Lives in its own broadcast frame
    (`notifications_avatar_button_label_frame`) so the button stays
    stable across notification arrivals — replacing the label leaves
    the focusable button intact, so clicks landing during a broadcast
    still hit a live element.

    Accepts an optional pre-computed `summary:` local so a parent
    partial (e.g. `_user_menu.html.erb`) can share ONE
    `unread_notification_breakdown` query across the avatar button,
    the bell, and the menu count span. Falls back to its own query
    when rendered standalone (e.g. via Turbo Stream broadcast). %>
<% summary ||= unread_notification_summary(user) %>
<span id="user_menu_button_label" class="sr-only">
  <%= avatar_button_aria_label(user, summary) %>
</span>
